    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix integer truncation in MIB configuration handling\n\n### Summary\nThe `update_mib_conf` function in the NR UE MAC layer was performing direct assignments of MIB fields without ensuring proper type compatibility. This led to integer truncation when wider integer types from the source MIB were assigned to narrower types in the target MIB structure.\n\nThe issue manifested downstream in `nr_ue_decode_mib` where invalid values caused incorrect frame number calculations and SSB offset handling. In some cases with malformed MIB data, this could lead to incorrect cell selection decisions.\n\nThis fix adds proper masking operations to ensure MIB fields stay within their ASN.1 specification ranges before assignment.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_UE/config_ue.c`: Added masking for `ssb_SubcarrierOffset`, `controlResourceSetZero`, and `searchSpaceZero` fields in `update_mib_conf` function to prevent integer truncation.\n\n"
}